## How to use me

1. **Type a question** in the box below — natural language, full sentences are fine.
2. **Watch the 🔬 Research disclosure** as I work. I'll search the corpus, drill into specific documents when needed, and pull surrounding context. You can expand it to see exactly what I read.
3. **Read my answer.** Each factual claim has a **[N]** marker.
4. **Click any [N]** or expand the **Sources** block at the bottom to see the original passage, source filename, and (when available) page number.
5. **Ask follow-ups.** I remember the last several turns of our conversation, so "tell me more about that" or "what about prescribed fire?" works naturally.

